{"tier":5,"question":"What is the St. Petersburg Paradox?","answer":"A game with infinite expected value that people will only pay a small sum to play, challenging expected utility theory","choices":["A pricing problem in Russian oil markets","A game with infinite expected value that people will only pay a small sum to play, challenging expected utility theory","A paradox in international trade theory","A problem in general equilibrium theory"]},
