{"tier":5,"question":"What is the diamond-water paradox?","answer":"Water is essential but cheap; diamonds are trivial but expensive — explained by marginal utility","choices":["Essential goods are always priced lower than luxury goods","Water is essential but cheap; diamonds are trivial but expensive — explained by marginal utility","Natural resources are always underpriced","The price of a good reflects its total utility"]},
